prompt.user:
Project: {project_name} Client: {client_name} Methodology: {methodology} Service Lines: {service_lines}
Project Type Guidance: {project_type_guidance}
SOW Summary: {sow_summary}
Service Line Design Standards: {standards_context}
Platform Combination Patterns (proven integration patterns for this service line mix): {combinations_context}
Generated Requirements Context (if available): {requirements_context}
FORMAT GUIDE ONLY — READ CAREFULLY BEFORE GENERATING: The example below is for a COMPLETELY DIFFERENT fictional project (Meridian Insurance). DO NOT copy any of the following from the example into your output: - Layer names (ClaimsPortal, MuleSoft Integration Layer, Policy Sync Worker) - Error categories or messages specific to the fictional project - Numbers (3 retries, 60-second timeout, 500ms) unless they appear in THIS project's context - Technology names unless they also appear in THIS project's service lines above The example shows ONLY the structure and depth of each section. All content must come from the actual project context above.
FORMAT EXAMPLE (fictional project — structure only):
### Error Categories | Category | Examples | Handling Strategy | User Impact | |----------|----------|------------------|-------------| | [Error type specific to THIS project's integrations] | [Actual API/service errors from THIS stack] | [Retry / fallback / fail-fast specific to the service] | [What the end user sees] |
#### [Layer Name — use actual component names from THIS project's service lines] - **Error types**: [Errors specific to THIS layer — e.g. if Salesforce: governor limits, SOQL failures; if ServiceNow: REST API timeouts] - **Handling approach**: [Specific to the framework in use — name the actual error handling mechanism] - **Retry strategy**: [Backoff intervals relevant to THIS service's SLA requirements] - **Fallback**: [What happens when retries are exhausted — specific to THIS project's business rules] - **Logging**: [Log level + what fields are captured — tied to the logging tool in THIS project's stack]
END OF FORMAT EXAMPLE.
Now generate the error handling strategy for {project_name} — client {client_name}, service lines: {service_lines}. Every layer name, error type, and retry strategy must come from the actual project context above. Do not copy names or numbers from the format example. Do NOT add a "Note:" section or any closing assumptions paragraph. Output ONLY markdown.
